<div id="review_4119234142" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4119234142" />
    <a title="Andrew Wardle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/104024055-andrew-wardle"><img alt="Andrew Wardle" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4119234142?book_show_action=true">Jul 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew Wardle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew Wardle" href="/user/show/104024055-andrew-wardle">Andrew Wardle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4119234142" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9897323731124649786">Very good, but too short.<br/>A war veteran tells a young man the story of his brother&apos;s death. Lieutenant Schelling, a sensitive and intelligent conscript officer, hates the Army and the German leadership, and makes enemies by his efforts to improve the conditions of his men and expose profiteering and corruption in the supply services. Its only faults were that it was very short at 130 pages (Boll served throughout WWII and might have been expected to have more material to work into a book about mi</span>
  <span id="freeText9897323731124649786" style="display:none">Very good, but too short.<br />A war veteran tells a young man the story of his brother's death. Lieutenant Schelling, a sensitive and intelligent conscript officer, hates the Army and the German leadership, and makes enemies by his efforts to improve the conditions of his men and expose profiteering and corruption in the supply services. Its only faults were that it was very short at 130 pages (Boll served throughout WWII and might have been expected to have more material to work into a book about military service), and that the plot denouement is very literal. But humane and thoughtful.<br />Some great lines: the men "practising the movements they had ceased to master because they had been practising them too long";<br />"Monotony is the most effective weapon of modern warfare";<br />"If there were nothing but infantrymen......there would be no more war";<br />"People go on living because of their weak memory";<br />(on pilferers' fear of being caught): "whenever a shell bursts close by, people are scared"<br />"This fear (of being taken prisoner by the Russians) alone prevented the war in Russia from ending in 1942" </span>
  <a data-text-id="9897323731124649786" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


