<div id="review_3352887594" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3352887594" />
    <a title="Tom" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6527128-tom"><img alt="Tom" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3352887594?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tom" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tom" href="/user/show/6527128-tom">Tom</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3352887594" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10958265534286116674">Böll&apos;s first novel, and one that remained unpublished for over 40 years. Böll captures the boredom and fear of troops in a war they suspect is already lost and that will not be affected in any way by their sacrifices. I like most of Böll&apos;s work, and in particular the stories based on his wartime experiences, because of the insight they provide about Germany and Germans. This short novel was no exception.</span>
  <span id="freeText10958265534286116674" style="display:none">Böll's first novel, and one that remained unpublished for over 40 years. Böll captures the boredom and fear of troops in a war they suspect is already lost and that will not be affected in any way by their sacrifices. I like most of Böll's work, and in particular the stories based on his wartime experiences, because of the insight they provide about Germany and Germans. This short novel was no exception.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10958265534286116674" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


